import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    monthly_avg_temp = data.groupby('month')['temperature'].mean()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(monthly_avg_temp.index, monthly_avg_temp.values)
    
    plt.title("What is the average temperature distribution in Seattle throughout the year?")
    plt.xlabel("Month")
    plt.ylabel("Average Temperature")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

    data['MONTH'] = data['DATE'].dt.month

    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:

    return plt;
